@{U}1.1  About the Tera Desktop                                   TeraDesk@{u}  
  
Tera  Desktop  is  a  replacement  for  the  ST, STE or TT desktop. It  
provides  more  facilities  than  the standard TOS desktop (especially  
the  one  in TOS versions 1.*) and windows are drawn and scrolled much  
faster  in it; It allows icons for files and programs and provides the  
ability to view files in windows.  
  
TeraDesk  was  initially  developed  by  Wout Klaren. Version 1.41 was  
released in '94 and here the development stopped for some time.  
  
Version  1.42 was the first one published (in the year 2002) under the  
GPL.  
  
Version  2.0  was  an  adaptation  by H. Robbers to modern AES's (like  
N.Aes,  XaAES  &  MagiC);  A  single  binary runs on ALL environments.  
However,  a  somewhat  smaller  binary compiled for Single-TOS only is  
included  too,  for  the benefit of users with machines having minimum  
RAM.  
  
Version  2.3  was  the first result of joined efforrts of Henk Robbers  
and Djordje Vukovic, comprising a number of new features.  
  
Version  3.0  is  the result of continued cooperation of H.Robbers and  
Dj.Vukovic;  it  is  a  significant  further improvement of TeraDesk's  
functionality, the program having undergone a significant redesign.  
  
  
The program may be copied and distributed freely provided:  
  
1.  All  the files listed below are copied and distributed at the same  
time and none are changed in any way.  
  
2.  The  program  is  not  sold  without the written permission of the  
authors.  If  the  program  is  distributed  by a PD library, only the  
costs of the disk and distribution may be recovered.  
  
The Tera Desktop files (included in the binary distribution) are:  
  
             DESKTOP.PRG      The Tera Desktop program  
             DESKTOS.PRG      Reduced version for single TOS only  
             DESKTOP.RSC      English resource file  
             DESKTOP.RSD      English resource definitions file  
             ICONS.RSC        Monochrome icons resource file  
             CICONS.RSC       Colour icons resource file  
             README.TXT       Instructions in English  
             HIST_V3.TXT      Version changes in English  
             TERADESK.HYP     ST-Guide manual in English  
             TERADESK.REF     Reference file for the above  
             TERADESK.INF     Sample configuration file 
             TERADESK.PAL     Sample palette file 
             TERADESK.BAT     Sample startup file 
             COPYING          Copy of the GPL  
  
@endnode  
  
  
