@{U}1.2.1  Hardware requirements                                  TeraDesk@{u}  
  
Tera  Desktop  can  be  used on any Atari ST series computer and their  
offspring,  TT,  Falcon,  Hades, Milan or emulators. It uses about 200  
KB of memory.  
  
Although  Tera Desktop can be used without the aid of a hard disk, the  
use  of  one  is  strongly  recommended.  This  is because the program  
should  be available on disk at all times when it is running in single  
TOS.  This  requirement  can  be  facilitated,  if you have sufficient  
memory, by placing it in a RAM disk.  
  
@endnode  
  
