@node "Copy disk..."  
@toc "Menu title: File"  
@image udo_fo.img 1  
   Contents  
@image udo_fo.img 4  
      Menus and Dialogues  
@image udo_fo.img 7  
         Menu title: File  
  
@{U}4.2.12 Copy disk...                                           TeraDesk@{u}  
  
When  this  item is selected and a floppy drive icon is also selected, 
a  physical copy, sector by sector, of the floppy will be made. Before 
attempting  actual  copying, a check will be made to see if the target 
and  the  source disk have the same format. Therefore, both disks must 
have  valid  boot  sectors containing the information on the number of 
sides, tracks and sectors. 
  
For copying, a buffer of the size specified in Copy and print...  
options will be used.  
  
If  this  operation  is  used  in  a multitasking environment (Mint or 
Magic),  an  attempt  is  made  to lock the floppy drive device before 
commencing copying. 
  
Note  that  this item might not be present in the copy of TeraDesk you 
are  using,  i.e.  it is possible to compile Tera Desktop without this 
function. See also Screen resolutions. 
  
  
@endnode  
  
  
@node "Format disk..."  
@toc "Menu title: File"  
@image udo_fo.img 1  
   Contents  
@image udo_fo.img 4  
      Menus and Dialogues  
@image udo_fo.img 7  
         Menu title: File  
  
@{U}4.2.13 Format disk...                                         TeraDesk@{u}  
  
When this item is selected and a floppy drive icon is also selected,  
the dialogue of the Floppy format function appears on the screen.  
  
The dialogue offers many options:  
  
4 densities:  
     Single sided    (SSDD)  
     Double sided    (DSDD)  
     High density    (DSHD)  
     Extra density   (DSED)  
  
For each density chosen, further parameters can be specified:  
  
    number of sides  
    number of tracks  
    number of sectors per tracks  
    directory size  
    volume label  
      
If  this  operation  is  used  in  a multitasking environment (Mint or 
Magic),  an  attempt  is  made  to lock the floppy drive device before 
commencing formatting.  If it fails  (e.g. if the device is already in
use), formatting can not be commenced.
      
Note  that  this item might not be present in the copy of TeraDesk you 
are  using,  i.e.  it is possible to compile Tera Desktop without this 
function. See also Screen resolutions. 
  
@endnode  
  
@node "Quit/Shutdown"  
@toc "Menu title: File"  
@image udo_fo.img 1  
   Contents  
@image udo_fo.img 4  
      Menus and Dialogues  
@image udo_fo.img 7  
         Menu title: File  
  
@{U}4.2.13 Quit/Shutdown                                          TeraDesk@{u}  
  
Select this item to quit Tera Desktop and:  
1: return to the standard desktop   
2: return to the AES fallback desktop (N.Aes or XaAES)  
3: shut down the computer completely  
   In a multitasking environment the appropriate shutdown procedure  
   is activated.  
     
Note  that  only  a  most  general  sequence of shutdown operations is 
performed:  shutdown is invoked by shel_write(...) function, which may 
not  have  any  effect in older versions of the AES. After shel_write, 
and  after  waiting for several seconds, if TeraDesk is still alive, a 
reset is performed. 
   
If  a  more  sophisticated  shutdown  is required, a separate Shutdown 
utility should be used. 
   
     
@endnode  
  
  
