@{U}4.3.1  Show as...                                             TeraDesk@{u}  
  
One  or  the  other  of  'Show  as  icons'  or  'Show  as text' may be 
selected.  The  selected option is ticked. Files and folders are shown 
in the Directory windows as icons or as text respectively. 
  
In  text mode, the length in bytes, the creation date and time and the 
file attributes can be shown as well as the file name. 
  
Which  of  the  above  are  shown is determined by the Show options in 
this menu. 
  
@endnode  
  
  
@node "Sort by..."  
@toc "Menu title: View"  
@image udo_fo.img 1  
   Contents  
@image udo_fo.img 4  
      Menus and Dialogues  
@image udo_fo.img 7  
         Menu title: View  
  
@{U}4.3.2  Sort by...                                             TeraDesk@{u}  
  
With these items you can select the order in which the files displayed   
in a window are sorted. The possibilities are:  
  
               1.   Sort by name  
               2.   Sort by extension  
               3.   Sort by creation date  
               4.   Sort by size  
               5.   View unsorted  
  
Items  are sorted in the ascending order. Note that, in 'Sort by size' 
mode,  this  is  contrary  to  the  TOS  desktop which lists first the 
largest files. 
  
If  you  select  'View  unsorted', items are displayed in the order in 
which  they  were stored on the disk; this corresponds to the order in 
which  they were placed on the disk; note that this is not necessarily 
the same as the order of their creation dates. 
  
The mode selected applies to all open windows.  
  
@endnode  
  
  
@node "Show options"  
@toc "Menu title: View"  
@image udo_fo.img 1  
   Contents  
@image udo_fo.img 4  
      Menus and Dialogues  
@image udo_fo.img 7  
         Menu title: View  
  
@{U}4.3.3  Show options                                           TeraDesk@{u}  
  
With  these  items  you  can  select  the  amount of information shown 
alongside  the object name when in text mode. The selected options are 
ticked.  
 
               1.   Show size  
               2.   Show date  
               3.   Show time  
               4.   Show attributes  
  
Selection applies to all open directory windows.  
  
The attributes which are set are denoted as follows:  
  
               d        directory  
               -        permission not granted or attribute not set.  
  
For TOS file systems:  
               s        system file  
               h        hidden file  
               w        writable file (NOT write protected)  
               a        archive bit  
  
For VFAT or UNIX file systems:  
  
              l         link  
                
        repeated for user, group and world:  
  
              r        read permission  
              w        write permission  
              x        execute permission  
  
@endnode  
  
  
@node "Set mask..."  
@toc "Menu title: View"  
@image udo_fo.img 1  
   Contents  
