      Menus and Dialogues  
@image udo_fo.img 7  
         Menu title: View  
  
@{U}4.3.4  Set mask...                                            TeraDesk@{u}  
  
With  this  item,  you can select which files are shown in the current 
(top)  directory  window. A dialog box is displayed into which you can 
either  type  a  file  mask  or  select a mask from a predefined list. 
Double  clicking  on  a  mask  in  the  list  has the double effect of 
selecting the mask and exiting the box as if you selected 'OK'. 
  
It  is  also  possible  to  delete the mask which is selected, edit an 
existing mask or add a new one to the list. See The listbox dialogue. 
  
The  selected  mask  ONLY  applies  to  the directory window  that was 
current (Top) when this item was selected.  
 
Alongside a mask, four other masking options can be chosen.  
  
     Hidden              show hidden files  
     System              show system files  
     Subfolders          show subfolders  
     Parent              show the .. (parent) virtual folder  
       
These selections are global, i.e. they apply to ALL directory windows. 
 
       
@endnode  
  
  
