@{U}4.4.6  Desk preferences...                                    TeraDesk@{u}  
  
- Set the dialog box display mode:  
   Dialogue boxes can be drawn in one of three modes.  
   Each mode has its advantages:  
  
    1. Normal (like TOS desktop) mode.  
       None of the special features associated with the other modes   
       are available. Dialogues are fixed to the original position.  
         
    2. Flying (or buffered mode).  
       In this mode, the screen under a dialogue box is saved in a   
       buffer. It can thus be restored rapidly if the box is moved or   
       resized. In this mode it is possible to move a dialogue box   
       about the screen by clicking on a special button (the 'ear')  
       in its top right corner.  
  
    3. Window mode.  
       In this mode, dialogue boxes appear in windows. This has the   
       advantage that you can use accessories while the box is   
       displayed and can move the dialogue box about the screen.  
  
Note that dialogue boxes displayed by other programs are not effected.  
  
  
- Determine the position of the dialog box:  
   There are two possibilities:  
  
    1. Under mouse  
       Place the box at a point determined by the position of the mouse.   
       This option is of most use when the display of the box is  
       initiated by a key press.  
  
       It is thus possible to prevent it covering other objects.  
  
    2. Centered  
       Centre the box on the screen in the standard way.  
  
- Specify menu shortcuts:  
  
    Use the arrows for choosing a menu item.  
    Then fill out the key you want to use as shortcut for this menu.  
    Plain keys are possible, just type the key.  
    Combinations with CTRL are possible, prepend the key by ^  
    Some of the special keys can be used, which should be entered  
    in text form as TAB, BS, DEL and SP for the [Tab], [Backspace],  
    [Delete] and [Space] keys.  
      
    Note that, because of the limitations of the  scan codes  of the  
    Atari keyboards, some key combinations can not be differentiated  
    from some others, and some will be recognized as illegal.   
  
- Set the default tabsize:  
  
    The number of blank column produced in a text window when a 'Tab'  
    is encountered. This is the global setting; Tab size for each of   
    the Text windows can be set in the menu of that window.  
  
@endnode  
  
  
  
